# selectors
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
input[type="text"] {
  width: 150px;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  background-color: yellow;
}

input[type="button"] {
  width: 100px;
  margin-left: 35px;
  display: block;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<form name="input" action="" method="get">
  Firstname:<input type="text" name="Name" value="Navya" size="20">
  Lastname:<input type="text" name="Name" value="Palle" size="20">
  <input type="button" value="Submit">
</form>

</body>
</html>


http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/


# navigation-bars
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<p>In this example, we remove the bullets from the list, and its default padding and margin.</p>
<p>Each and every navigation bar will direct you to their respective pages.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
  <li><a href="#registration">Registration</a></li>
  <li><a href="#Personal Details">Personal Details</a></li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>
